description: Apple HIG guidance for macOS-first UI work in this Electron app
globs:
  - src/**/*.ts
  - src/**/*.tsx
  - src/**/*.css
  - electron/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use the Apple HIG skill for UI, UX, layout, motion, color, typography, iconography, and accessibility decisions.
- Treat this repository as a macOS desktop product first. Prefer macOS patterns, then general Apple principles.
- Keep interfaces clear, restrained, accessible, and native-feeling.
- Favor sidebars, split views, tables, toolbars, inspectors, and keyboard-friendly interactions over mobile-first patterns.
- Respect reduced motion, semantic colors, and readable spacing.

